cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper deals with image collections and their organization, cleaning, and labeling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses supervised and unsupervised learning methods, which are relevant to categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of human assistance in the labeling process suggests a connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the large dataset of images and the focus on image analysis could also place this paper in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
